args: Enough, Your Highness. It's noon.\nThat's more than enough training\nfor one day.
Whew! You may be right about that.
You really are incredible, Elly.\nYour guard is flawless.
No matter what angle I used, you were\nready. It's like you have eyes in the\nback of your head.
If I'm being honest, you could stand to be\nmore like that.
You focus far too much on what's in\nfront of you.
Unchivalrous fiends will happily strike\nan unguarded back if they can.\nYou must pay closer attention.
But aren't you there to protect my back?
I can afford to focus on what's in front of\nme because I know all of you are covering\nmy blind spots.
I suppose that makes a...\ncertain amount of sense.
But do you not find it unbecoming\nfor a member of the royal family\nto be so dependent?
And I personally think it improper\nfor a king or knight to willingly\nexpose themselves so eagerly.
Regardless, as the duty of both royalty and\nknights is to help the people, you should—
Ha! That's hilarious comin' from you,\nMs. Perfect Paladyn!
Ain't no need to be so stubborn\nabout everything.
Besides, out on the battlefield,\nit's important to have pals what\ncan cover yer blind spots.
I'm not trying to understate the\nimportance of allies in battle.
I'm just pointing out what I believe to be\na flaw in the prince's way of thinking.
Are the other Paladyns all like you?
We're entrusted to guard the Auspex—\nno one will come along and perform\nthis duty for us.
Well, I can't fault ya for takin' your\njob seriously—even if a life without\nfun ain't really one worth livin'.
There's no need to speak of me as\nif I'm a loveless hermit with no\nconcept of hobbies or joy.
There ARE things I do for fun,\nafter all.
I didn't know you had a pet.
Oh my, that's easy. It eats... Um... \nActually, my pet requires no\nsustenance.
You have an animal that doesn't need\nto eat?
Ah! I understand our problem now.\nYou were speaking of real animals.\nI was referring to ornamental ones.
Leave it to a stubborn knight to be\ninto some animal-shaped rock.
I betcha use it as a sparring partner\nor a target dummy or—
I do no such thing, sir!\nMy animal is cuuu...uuuu...
Cuuuu...t? Cut! Yes, cut. I meant to\nsay that it's cut from animal hide.\nEr, I think.
Just seeing it brightens my day!
Now if that is all of your questions,\nI bid you good day.
She was leaving before she was even\ndone talking.
Now THERE'S a lady with a secret!
